citeinfo.title: Koppen Climate Classification for the Conterminous United States

descript.abstract: The Koppen Climate Classification grid coverages were produced using gridded estimates of precipitation, temperature, and elevation from the PRISM (Parameter-elevation Regressions on Independent Slopes Model). The model was developed at Oregon State University and information about the gridded ASCII data sets can be obtained from: http://www.ocs.orst.edu/prism/.
descript.purpose: To use spatially gridded data from the PRISM project to delineate climate zones based on the Koeppen Climate Classification Criteria. The criteria used to delineate the zones may be obtained from: http://snow.ag.uidaho.edu/Clim_Map/criteria.html.
descript.supplinf:
Procedures_Used: 1. Aquired the PRISM ASCII files from Oregon Climate Service (http://www.ocs.orst.edu/prism/).
2. Aquired the United State boundary coverage (1:2,000,000) from the GAP Analysis Project Office at the University of Idaho http://www.wildlife.uidaho.edu/). This coverage was orignally obtained by GAP from the ESRI data site (www.esri.com).
3. Ran the main aml (koeppen.aml) to produce the classification.
4. Merged the individual grids into one grid containing the lowest subclasses.

An error in the classes.aml was discovered by Ben Logan at Virginia Tech. It was discovered in the creation of the B parameters that an "or" should have been an "&". An "or" was replaced with an "&" on line 3.
Code before error discovered: Class B if (pptsummer70 >= 0.7 & ppt14 < (2 * tavg14 + 28) & temp/tempA <> 1 or ~ pptwinter70 >= 0.7 & ppt14 < (2 * tavg14) & temp/tempA <> 1 or ~ pptsummer70 < 0.7 & ppt14 < (2 * tavg14 + 14) & temp/tempA <> 1 or ~ pptwinter70 < 0.7 & ppt14 < (2 * tavg14 + 14) & temp/tempA <> 1) endif
Code after error corrected: Class B if (pptsummer70 >= 0.7 & ppt14 < (2 * tavg14 + 28) & temp/tempA <> 1 or ~ pptwinter70 >= 0.7 & ppt14 < (2 * tavg14) & temp/tempA <> 1 or ~ pptsummer70 < 0.7 & ppt14 < (2 * tavg14 + 14) & temp/tempA <> 1 & ~ pptwinter70 < 0.7 & ppt14 < (2 * tavg14 + 14) & temp/tempA <> 1) endif
